  <description><![CDATA[<p>The luxurious décor and facilities of the Grand Rousses celebrate the very best of mountain lifestyle. The hotel has signed up to the U<span>nited Nations Global Compact, a voluntary commitment to advance their approach to social responsibility.  </span>The family-run hotel prides itself on a high standard of service and a warm and friendly welcome is assured. From arrival to departure, you will have the designated concierge service on hand to meet any requirements or needs you may have. </p>
<h2>Ski in/ ski out access</h2>
<p>Located in the centre of <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/ski-holidays/ski-resorts/france/alpe-dhuez">Alpe d'Huez</a>, the Grandes Rousses Hotel &amp; Spa has ski in/ ski out access. Perfect for those who are keen to get out on the mountain first thing and return when the lifts close for the day. The hotel has an incredible location in the resort, with breath-taking views of the mountain peeks surrounding Alpe d'Huez.</p>
<h2>A cosy mountain retreat</h2>
<p>With a range of accommodation, the hotel design has been influenced by an alpine chalet, easy to live in, intergenerational, cosy and warm. The spacious and bright rooms offer an enchanting atmosphere, many of the rooms have exceptional views of the alpine peaks and a range of high quality facilities. </p>
<p>The hotel has two restaurants both of which are committed to using local produce and creating dishes influenced by the 'Isère' region. Half board meals are taken in the <span>L'Espérance restaurant, where the menu is inspired by traditional French cuisine with a modern twist - choose to dine in the modern panoramic restaurant or in the unique private dining bubbles, be sure to reserve your pod at reception. If you are looking for a spot for lunch or want to dine à la carte, La Ferme d'Hubert is a great choice - the seasonal menu draws inspiration from nature, utilising local products from the region to create a delicious dishes to be enjoyed on the sunny terrace or in the modern brassiere style restaurant. At the end of the day, you can also enjoy sampling wine and platters of charcuterie and cheese sourced from neighbouring farms at Aux Grands Rouges Lounge Bar.</span><span></span></p>
<h2>Unwind and relax</h2>
<p>Residents have complimentary access to the Terrasse d'Hubert wellness area which has an outdoor heated pool, jacuzzi and heated sauna, perfect for giving yourself a break after a day exploring <a data-udi="umb://document/acff50eb9ad84862a464f68b551bc497" href="/{localLink:umb://document/acff50eb9ad84862a464f68b551bc497}" title="Alpe d'Huez">Alpe d'Huez</a>.</p>
<p>The Spa des Alpes is the perfect place to pamper yourself, reserve your 45 minute spot for a local fee, and enjoy the sensory pool, copper baths, cryotherapy equipment, sensory showers, ice fountain, sauna, hammam and tea room. The spa is adults open daily, so you can fully relax without any interruptions.</p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
