  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Classic double rooms</strong> are 22m² and sleep two people. They have a king-size or twin beds and an East or North facing balcony with a view of the village or the mountains. These rooms are available for sole occupancy on request, please call to book.</p>
<p><strong>Panoramic rooms</strong> are 24m² and sleep two people with a king-sized or twin beds, desk and armchair, and have a south facing balcony with panoramic views over the resort towards the mountains.</p>
<p><strong>Prestige rooms</strong> are around 31m² and sleep two to three people with a double bed or twin beds, and additional bed for a child. These rooms have <span>mountain or village views. </span></p>
<p>Panoramic rooms, Deluxe rooms and Suites also have Bluetooth speakers as well as multiple charging and USB points.</p>
<p><strong>Room facilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>King-sized or twin beds, please let us know if you have a preference</li>
<li>Free Wi-Fi</li>
<li>Tassimo or Nespresso machine for tea and coffee</li>
<li>Mini bar</li>
<li>Satellite TV with English speaking channels</li>
<li>Bathroom with bath and shower head attachment</li>
<li>Toiletries</li>
<li>WC</li>
<li>Safe</li>
<li>Interconnecting rooms are available on request</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>]]></roomsDescription>
